                <note rend="inline" type="source">667.003/124: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-06-21T18:00:00+03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1921—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 22—9:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>203. My telegram number 190, June 7, 5 p.m. Turkish Government informally
                    indicates willingness to revert to pre-war system of taxation in case the powers
                    will consent to a temporary increase in ad valorem rate to 14 or 15 percent to
                    meet urgent needs of Treasury, (see Department’s telegram 86 of November
                        15th<note n="10" xml:id="d861fn10">
                        <ref target="frus1920v03#pg_765">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1920, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 765</ref>.</note>), this increase to
                    be enforced until final determination of tariff system under peace treaty.</p>
                <p>I consider this most opportune moment for bringing pressure to bear in London,
                    Paris and Rome. Request information of action taken.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
